  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/559404248" />
    <a title="Ken Brimhall" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7964968-ken-brimhall"><img alt="Ken Brimhall" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442512178p2/7964968.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/559404248?book_show_action=true">Mar 12, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ken Brimhall" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ken Brimhall" href="/user/show/7964968-ken-brimhall">Ken Brimhall</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer559404248" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11351101762099924839"><br/>Thank you, Melodie Ramone, for NOT chopping up After Forever Ends and selling it in sequels, for it is most beautiful the way it is—a complete whole—love from adolescence to old age, love given freely and completely and returned in kind. No need for politics or religion, unless you count the faeries in the Welsh wood, which I do since I believe it was God speaking with Oliver and Silvia through the elves. What a unique and wonderful life to love one identical twin as a husband and the second as </span>
  <span id="freeText11351101762099924839" style="display:none"><br />Thank you, Melodie Ramone, for NOT chopping up After Forever Ends and selling it in sequels, for it is most beautiful the way it is—a complete whole—love from adolescence to old age, love given freely and completely and returned in kind. No need for politics or religion, unless you count the faeries in the Welsh wood, which I do since I believe it was God speaking with Oliver and Silvia through the elves. What a unique and wonderful life to love one identical twin as a husband and the second as a brother, despite the tragic events along the way. And to raise three beautiful children, isolated from the world really, where one could run naked through the garden, if one so desired. You have written a beautiful story, Melodie Ramone, and as we all know, BEAUTY will save the world. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11351101762099924839" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
