<div id="review_476634646" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/476634646" />
    <a title="Janice Ross" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12668584-janice-ross"><img alt="Janice Ross" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1457229360p2/12668584.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/476634646?book_show_action=true">Dec 12, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Janice Ross" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Janice Ross" href="/user/show/12668584-janice-ross">Janice Ross</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer476634646" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10498872123314131634">One of my favorite quotes from AFTER FOREVER ENDS is &quot;Love is the oldest and greatest of all the magic in the world.&quot; I open up my review with this quote because Melodie Ramone&apos;s novel is absolutely magical. True love - the high, lows and in-between is captured in this remarkable novel about Oliver Dickinson and Just Silvia Cotton (you have to read it to understand this reference). After Forever Ends is not only a splendid journey of love, it&apos;s a lifetime of living set on display for all to expe</span>
  <span id="freeText10498872123314131634" style="display:none">One of my favorite quotes from AFTER FOREVER ENDS is "Love is the oldest and greatest of all the magic in the world." I open up my review with this quote because Melodie Ramone's novel is absolutely magical. True love - the high, lows and in-between is captured in this remarkable novel about Oliver Dickinson and Just Silvia Cotton (you have to read it to understand this reference). After Forever Ends is not only a splendid journey of love, it's a lifetime of living set on display for all to experience.<br /><br />Thank you Melodie Ramone, for sharing this beautifully written tale. I look forward to many more.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10498872123314131634" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
