<div id="review_527265452" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/527265452" />
    <a title="S. Conde" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12290079-s-conde"><img alt="S. Conde" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442642291p2/12290079.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/527265452?book_show_action=true">Feb 05, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="S. Conde" class="user" itemprop="url" name="S. Conde" href="/user/show/12290079-s-conde">S. Conde</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer527265452" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12315361499314989435">I genuinely enjoyed &quot;After Forever Ends&quot;. Ms. Ramone spins an enchanting and highly emotional tale around the themes, of love, loss, family, and magic. The author writes of both the joyous, predestined love affair between Oliver and Silvia, and the heartbreaking losses they experience in a way only someone who has known love and loss intimately can. Honestly. ...of the faeries... Beautiful, and just enough. They set the magical tone of the story without becoming ridiculous. The characters of Sil</span>
  <span id="freeText12315361499314989435" style="display:none">I genuinely enjoyed "After Forever Ends". Ms. Ramone spins an enchanting and highly emotional tale around the themes, of love, loss, family, and magic. The author writes of both the joyous, predestined love affair between Oliver and Silvia, and the heartbreaking losses they experience in a way only someone who has known love and loss intimately can. Honestly. ...of the faeries... Beautiful, and just enough. They set the magical tone of the story without becoming ridiculous. The characters of Silvia, Alexander, and Oliver were strong; I was happy to spend my time with them. A word to the wise, have tissues on hand. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12315361499314989435" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
